author: Melissa Hoyer
title: David Gandy in Sydney, Australia for Dolce & Gabbana mens cologne
text:
FROM vowing never to do a fashion show ever again, Essex-born uber model David Gandy is the real deal.
Clever, charming, down-to-earth, witty, and yes, yes, yes, handsome, this 35-year-old is one clever cookie.
“When I did my first fashion week in Milan when I was 22, which I hoped to be my last, as fashion weeks are just horrendous,” says David.
David Gandy attends a photo call to launch his collection for Marks and Spencer Autograph at M&S in London. Picture: Tristan Fewings / Getty Images
David Gandy joins Bowmont Merino and Exmoor Horn sheep grazing the length of Savile Row to mark the launch of Wool Week 2015 in London. Picture: Tristan Fewings / Getty Images
Nick Grimshaw, Jamal Edwards, Tom Meighan, Serge Pizzorno and David Gandy sit in the front row at Burberry Menswear show in London. Picture: Samir Hussein / Getty Images
Mr Gandy at the amfAR's Cinema Against AIDS Gala in Cap d'Antibes this year. Picture: Tristan Fewings / Getty Images
Mollie King and David Gandy attend the annual BGC Global Charity Day at BGC Partners on September 11, 2015 in London. Picture: Fred Duval / Getty Images
